## Additional Notices

This project is a fan-made work based on:

- **The Magnus Archives** podcast by Rusty Quill (https://rustyquill.com)
- **The Magnus Archives Roleplaying Game** by Monte Cook Games (https://www.montecookgames.com)

This software has **no official affiliation** with Rusty Quill or Monte Cook Games.

### Third-Party Assets & Licenses

#### Artwork

- Avatar portrait frames and design elements by kruk-art (https://kruk-art.tumblr.com)
- Used with permission for fan projects

#### 3D Dice Roller

- Dice roller system by Sarah Rosanna Busch (https://sarahrosannabusch.ca/)
- Original work by Anton Natarov
- Uses three.js (MIT License) - https://github.com/mrdoob/three.js/
- Uses cannon.js (MIT License) - https://github.com/schteppe/cannon.js
- Sound effects from Nicovideo Commons (http://commons.nicovideo.jp/material/nc93322)

### Intellectual Property Rights

All rights to **The Magnus Archives** intellectual property, including characters,
settings, and storylines, belong to Rusty Quill.

All rights to the **Cypher System** and game mechanics belong to Monte Cook Games.

This license applies only to the original code and implementation of this character
sheet software, not to the underlying intellectual properties or game system.

### Usage Requirements

Users of this software must own or have access to **The Magnus Archives Roleplaying Game**
rulebook published by Monte Cook Games to play the game properly.

Purchase the official rulebook at:
https://www.montecookgames.com/store/product/the-magnus-archives-roleplaying-game/

